y having its CEO discuss individual accounts publicly, Twitter encouraged t=
he idea that account banning is subject to a single person's whims. Two, it=
 publicly undermined Twitter's communications team for the second time in a=
 year. Three, it inexplicably passed the buck for enforcing its policies to=
